This file is mostly historical at this point -- see TODO.md for the
current roadmap and BUGS for concrete, verified defects. Every item
that used to be here was investigated; most turned out to be either
already implemented or already fixed, and are gone from this list now
(see TODO.md's "old TODO file, investigated" section for the evidence
trail on each one). What's left is either a genuinely open, but too
broad/design-shaped to be a single "bug", item, or one I couldn't fully
verify.

Open design work (not bugs -- see TODO.md if you want these prioritized):

- simple line editing should be rewritten with a finer terminal
  abstraction and key-bindings
- terminal abstraction (for special capabilities etc.)
- key bindings

Needs verification (not confirmed with a live repro):

- glob check on subargs other than argstr: expand_arg.c does check the
  S_GLOB flag on nargstr sub-nodes the same way the top-level argstr
  path does, so this may already be handled -- didn't build a repro
  that proves or disproves a gap
